mov eax, [ebx+ecx*4]

This line of assembly code attempts to access memory at the address calculated by `ebx + ecx * 4`.  The bug arises when `ecx` is a very large value or is outside the bounds of the allocated memory for `ebx`. This can lead to a segmentation fault or other memory access violation, causing the program to crash.  Another potential problem is if `ebx` itself points to an invalid memory location.